_:N37d5baa2e288472bbe4ca0d234deeeb8 <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>The Government Communication Service is a <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-service/about/recruitment#professions\">Civil Service profession</a>. If you are working in communications, or need communications advice or support as part of your role, please get in touch.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"career-opportunities-and-professional-development\">Career opportunities and professional development</h2>\n\n<p>The <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://gcs.civilservice.gov.uk/\">Government Communication Service website</a> is the place where you can engage with your professional community and find out about the learning, qualifications and opportunities available to help you develop your skills.</p>\n\n<p>GCS offers a wide range of different learning opportunities, from traditional classroom-based learning and mentoring to case studies, guides and blog posts from cutting edge government communicators.</p>\n</div>" .
_:N6a576184732145f492843db90e910b9e <http://schema.org/name> "GOV.UK" .
_:N37d5baa2e288472bbe4ca0d234deeeb8 <http://schema.org/description> "We support all professional communicators across government to gain the skills and knowledge they need to carry out their roles." .
